Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper describes the design and development of an aerial robot with control and autonomy logic, which falls under the scope of robotics. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of a simulation environment and system identification to validate the feasibility of the flight mission, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions the use of autonomy logic in the design of the aerial robot, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper describes the development of the control and autonomy logic in the Simulink environment, which falls under the scope of software engineering. 
5. cs.ROBOTS (Robotics): The paper focuses on the design and development of a robot, which falls under the scope of robotics.
